---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="What is Artifacto, and why does it exist?" />
		<style>
			.about-content {
				max-width: 660px;
				margin: 0 auto;
			}
			.about-content h1 {
				background: var(--accent-gradient);
				-webkit-background-clip: text;
				-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
				background-clip: text;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
			}
			.about-content p {
				color: var(--text-secondary);
				line-height: 1.8;
			}
			.about-content a {
				color: var(--accent-light);
			}
			.feature-list {
				list-style: none;
				padding: 0;
				margin: 1.5rem 0;
			}
			.feature-list li {
				padding: 0.5em 0;
				color: var(--text-secondary);
				display: flex;
				align-items: baseline;
				gap: 0.5em;
			}
			.feature-list li::before {
				content: "◆";
				color: var(--accent);
				font-size: 0.7em;
				flex-shrink: 0;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<div class="about-content">
				<h1>About Artifacto</h1>
				<p>
					You spend an hour spelunking through stack traces with an AI agent, finally land the
					fix at 2am, feel briefly like a wizard — and then the chat scrolls away and the
					knowledge evaporates. Artifacto is the cure for that very specific kind of grief: it
					catches those ephemeral "aha" moments and fossilizes them into proper, searchable
					blog posts.
				</p>
				<p>
					Think of it as a lab notebook for the bugs you've slain, the workarounds you're not
					proud of, and the elegant solutions you absolutely are. Future-you will hit the same
					wall again — and this time there'll be a post waiting instead of a 404 in your memory.
				</p>

				<h2>How It Works</h2>
				<ul class="feature-list">
					<li>Throw in raw text, a markdown file, or a shared chat URL</li>
					<li>An LLM does the tedious part: turning rambling logs into a structured post</li>
					<li>You play editor — review, tweak, or veto before anything ships</li>
					<li>Approved posts deploy themselves via GitHub Pages, no humans in the loop</li>
				</ul>

				<p>
					Held together with <a href="https://astro.build/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a>,
					a bit of Python, and a healthy refusal to lose good ideas. Source code lives on
					<a href="https://github.com/padeler/artifacto" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>,
					bugs and all.
				</p>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
